The Telegraph - Calcutta

 AITA to adopt 12 children

New Delhi: The All India Tennis Association (AITA) will provide free tennis training to 12 tsunami-affected children aged between 10-12 and will also take care of their education expenses till matriculation. 

?The children will be selected from the affected areas of Andaman and Nicobar, Tamil Nadu and Pondicherry. They will be provided with all facilities including coaching and education free of cost till they finish 10th class standard or excel in the game,? an AITA press release said on Saturday. 

The kids will be trained at the National Tennis Academy in Gurgaon and those with special talent will be retained for a longer period. (PTI) 

